[2] Canada (Ontario)
Date: Mon 12 Sep 2016
Source: Windsor Square [edited]
http://www.windsorsquare.ca/archives/2016/ottawa-measles-outbreak-mitigated/96279


Ottawa [Ontario] measles outbreak mitigated
-------------------------------------------
Ottawa Public Health [OPH], in collaboration with Leeds, Grenville, and Lanark Health Unit and Public Health Ontario, have determined, through further laboratory analysis, that 1 of 3 identified cases of measles is negative. This is welcome news in the evolving investigation of the measles outbreak, as it reduces the locations where measles exposure may have occurred.

OPH will continue to work closely with partners in protecting the community from further spread of this very contagious disease and will provide public updates as required.

OPH is also reporting that the following locations previously identified in the public service announcement, issued on 3 Sep [2016], are no longer considered sites where exposure to measles may have occurred. [See list of locations at source URL.]

The risk of contracting measles in Ottawa is low for those who have been vaccinated. However, given that measles is highly contagious, it is very important that you ensure you and your loved ones' measles immunizations are up to date.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[While 1 less case may seem insignificant, because of the infectiousness of measles and how easily it spreads, it is good news.

Maps of Canada can be seen at http://mapsof.net/uploads/static-maps/Canada_Provinces_and_territories_map.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4489103,277. - Mod.LK]
